  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is defined by law as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions or legitimate businesses. Generally, it involves three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of money through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the money into the economy as seemingly legitimate funds\n\nThe specific legal definition can vary between jurisdictions, but most countries criminalize these activities under anti-money laundering (AML) statutes.",
